is not for us to talk about.

00:26:04.690 --> 00:26:06.600
We're going to bring the kitsch.

00:26:06.600 --> 00:26:08.550
And we think that's
a conversation

00:26:08.550 --> 00:26:10.410
other people should have.

00:26:10.410 --> 00:26:10.700
AUDIENCE: Let the think
piecers think piece.

00:26:10.700 --> 00:26:12.825
VIVIANA OLEN: But we
definitely aren't smart enough

00:26:12.825 --> 00:26:14.075
to sound smart about it.

00:26:14.075 --> 00:26:14.530
AUDIENCE: Oh, I don't
know if that's true.

00:26:14.530 --> 00:26:16.446
VIVIANA OLEN: Well
we-- but yeah.

00:26:16.446 --> 00:26:21.210
No, I mean I think like
the idea of Tonya and Nancy

00:26:21.210 --> 00:26:23.430
just being obliterated
by the media

00:26:23.430 --> 00:26:27.370
and it just ruined their
lives in so many ways.

00:26:27.370 --> 00:26:31.780
And same thing with
the Olsen twins.

00:26:31.780 --> 00:26:34.250
We want to bring the
fun aspect of it,

00:26:34.250 --> 00:26:39.720
and we definitely hope it gets
people talking and thinking

00:26:39.720 --> 00:26:41.910
about the seriousness
of it, because it

00:26:41.910 --> 00:26:48.042
is so jarring to celebrate
or have fun in that.

00:26:48.042 --> 00:26:50.250
MATT HARKINS: Yeah, that's
basically the conversation

00:26:50.250 --> 00:26:51.977
we had at first.

00:26:51.977 --> 00:26:53.560
When we first watched
the documentary,

00:26:53.560 --> 00:26:58.020
all we wanted to talk about was
how awful America treated Tonya

00:26:58.020 --> 00:26:59.729
